    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h1>The best thing that worked for me</h1> was delete the variables envioroment JAVA_HOME\nJDK_HOME STUDIO_OPTIONS etc, \n<p>all the variables related to ANDROID STUDIO AND JAVA</p>\n<p>I realized because I have another computer with android studio installed and working perfectly so I started to look up how were the variables there and it turned out that the computer didn't have any of those variables so I knew what was the problem</p>\n<p>however, I'll attach a screenshot of my variable environment state</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/YHHQu.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/YHHQu.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p><em>If this help you please i bet you like this post sorry if my english is a little bad but all are learning from each other</em></p>\n"
